# Quantum-Proof-Coin

It’s been a while since I actually sat down and built something from scratch.

After seeing other builders start shipping again, I got pulled back into it. And this time, I’m working on something that actually matters long-term.

I’m building a quantum-proof coin on Solana.

---

## Why

Right now, almost every chain relies on elliptic curve cryptography.

If quantum computing reaches the point where that gets cracked, everything changes:
- Wallets can be derived from public keys
- Funds can be drained
- Signatures stop meaning anything

That’s not some distant sci-fi scenario anymore. There’s already real probability being priced in that this happens sooner than people expect.

Nobody in the Solana ecosystem is seriously building for that at the infrastructure level.

So I am.

---

## What I’m doing

Not slapping “quantum resistant” on a token.

Not routing fees to some random dev.

Not copy pasting a GitHub repo I don’t understand.

I’m actually building this from scratch.

- Looking into post-quantum signature schemes
- Figuring out how they can realistically work with Solana
- Rethinking wallets, signing, and security from the ground up

This is going to be messy, difficult, and probably slow.

But it’ll be real.

